From the definitions:
- `g' = interpolated_deriv x y f`
- `interpolated_deriv x y f t = ∑ i, (y i - x i) * nth_partial i f ((1 - t) • x + t • y)`

So `g' 0 = ∑ i, (y i - x i) * nth_partial i f ((1 - 0) • x + 0 • y) = ∑ i, (y i - x i) * nth_partial i f x`

I need to bound this sum using the triangle inequality and the fact that `|x i - y i| ≤ ε`.

```lean
  have bound1 : |g' 0| ≤ ε * ∑ i, |nth_partial i f x|  := by
    unfold_let g'
    unfold interpolated_deriv
    simp only [one_smul, sub_zero, zero_smul, add_zero]
    calc |∑ i, (y i - x i) * nth_partial i f x|
        _ ≤ ∑ i, |( y i - x i) * nth_partial i f x| := abs_sum_le_sum_abs _ _
        _ = ∑ i, |y i - x i| * |nth_partial i f x| := by simp_all only [abs_mul]
        _ ≤ ∑ i, ε * |nth_partial i f x| := by
          apply Finset.sum_le_sum
          intro i _
          apply mul_le_mul_of_nonneg_right
          · rw [abs_sub_comm]; exact hdiff i
          · exact abs_nonneg _
        _ = ε * ∑ i, |nth_partial i f x| := by rw [← Finset.mul_sum]
```
